TITLE: Creating a Credits Table and Policy - Supabase SQL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates a \`public.credits\` table to record the number of tokens/credits for each user account. It applies row-level security (users can only see their own records) and creates a policy to expose only a user's own credits. This supports metered or credit-based billing scenarios in SaaS.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sahilpanhotra/makerkitdocs.git/blob/main/mdDocs/kits/api_billing_api_billing_schema_58.md#2025-04-22_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
create table public.credits (
  account_id uuid not null references public.accounts(id),
  tokens integer not null
);

alter table public.credits enable row level security;

-- allow authenticated users to read their credits
create policy read_credits
  on public.credits
  for select
  to authenticated
  using (
    account_id = (select auth.uid())
  );
```

