TITLE: Guarding Next.js Pages Based on Organization Subscription with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TSX code shows how to restrict access to a Next.js page based on the organization's subscription status within `getServerSideProps`. It utilizes `withAppProps` to fetch application data, including the organization's subscription details. A helper function `canAccessPage` checks if the `subscription.status` is either 'active' or 'trialing'. If the organization does not have an active or trialing subscription, the user is redirected to the '/dashboard'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sahilpanhotra/makerkitdocs.git/blob/main/mdDocs/kits/call_api_routes_from_client_csrf_token_guarding_api_routes_7.md#2025-04-22_snippet_17

