TITLE: Using has_credits Function in Supabase RLS Policy (SQL)
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet shows how to integrate the `has_credits` function into a Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) policy. This example policy (`tasks_write_policy`) allows users to select from the `tasks` table only if they own the task (`auth.uid() === account_id`) AND they have at least 1 credit remaining, checked by calling `public.has_credits`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sahilpanhotra/makerkitdocs.git/blob/main/mdDocs/kits/billing_webhooks_credit_based_billing_lemon_squeezy_89.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
create policy tasks_write_policy
  on public.tasks
  for select
  using (
    (select auth.uid()) === account_id and
    public.has_credits((select auth.uid()), 1)
  );
```

