TITLE: Performing Supabase Mutations with React Query (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the `useMutation` hook from `@tanstack/react-query` along with the `useSupabase` hook to perform data mutations (inserts) in a Supabase table (`tasks`). It defines a mutation function to insert a new task and demonstrates calling `mutateAsync` within a form submission handler. Dependencies include `@tanstack/react-query` and `@kit/supabase/hooks/use-supabase`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sahilpanhotra/makerkitdocs.git/blob/main/mdDocs/kits/csrf_protection_react_query_route_handlers_43.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
