TITLE: Creating a Custom Hook to Add Firestore Documents (TypeScript/React)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a React hook to add documents to a Firestore collection, wrapping the addDoc method inside useCallback for memoization. Depends on Firestore client library, a predefined TASKS_COLLECTION string, and React hooks. Expects a Task object as input and returns the promise from addDoc. Should be used inside React components to enable task creation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sahilpanhotra/makerkitdocs.git/blob/main/mdDocs/kits/custom_fetch_fetching_data_firestore_making_api_requests_4.md#2025-04-22_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { TASKS_COLLECTION } from '~/lib/firestore-collections';

function useCreateTask() {
  const firestore = useFirestore();
  const tasksCollection = collection(firestore, TASKS_COLLECTION);

  return useCallback(
    (task: Task) => {
      return addDoc(tasksCollection, task);
    },
    [tasksCollection]
  );
}
```

