TITLE: SQL Function to Count User Tasks
DESCRIPTION: SQL function that counts the number of tasks associated with a specific user ID. This function returns an integer representing the task count, which can be used for enforcing quota limits based on subscription plans.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sahilpanhotra/makerkitdocs.git/blob/main/mdDocs/kits/server_actions_uploading_data_to_storage_writing_data_to_supabase_30.md#2025-04-22_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
create or replace function get_user_task_count(user_id bigint)
returns int as $$
declare
    task_count int;
begin
    select count(*)
        from tasks
        where tasks.user_id = user_id
        into task_count;

    return task_count;
end;
$$ language plpgsql;
```

