TITLE: Defining a Supabase Query Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a reusable function `getOrganizationById` to fetch specific organization data from a Supabase table. It accepts a Supabase client instance and an organization ID as parameters, builds a query using the client's fluent API, selects specific columns (aliasing `logo_url` to `logoURL`), filters by ID, ensures errors are thrown, and expects a single result. This function is designed to be used in both server-side and client-side contexts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sahilpanhotra/makerkitdocs.git/blob/main/mdDocs/kits/architecture_auth_overview_auth_setup_29.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
 ```tsx {% title="organizations/queries.ts" %}
export function getOrganizationById(
  client: Client,
  organizationId: number
) {
  return client
    .from('organizations')
    .select(`
      id,
      name,
      logoURL: logo_url
    `)
    .eq('id', organizationId)
    .throwOnError()
    .single();
}
```
